# Retrieval eval experiment notes

Each `R00x-*.md` file has **two parts only**: hypothesis (before runs) and metrics (after runs). No third sections, no workflow state.

## 1. Гипотеза

- One general hypothesis — what changes vs [R001](research/steps/retrieval/eval/experiments/R001-dense-bge-baseline.md) and why it might help.
- Sub-variants **A, B, C, …** are a small formatting detail, not the story. One table: ID, `text_dense` pattern, short note, example. No narrative per letter, no outcomes, no "current code is B".
- **R001 is the baseline** — never label variant A as baseline or duplicate R001 metrics as row A.

## 2. Метрики

- One table, filled incrementally after MLflow runs: ID, run name/id, git commit, scalars.
- Do not add "Выводы", "next steps", or placeholders like "заполнить после прогонов".

## Do not put in the file

- Intermediate implementation status ("текущий код", "уже прогнано", регресс/улучшение в гипотезе).
- Per-variant postmortems — those belong in chat, commits, or MLflow, not in the experiment note until you add a dedicated conclusions pass (not part of the default template).
